---
export const prerender = true;
export const yilMeta = {
  date: '2026-05-06',
  headline: 'Execution Ends, Judgment Begins',
  summary:
    'Today AI tools got more room to run, information architecture was reaffirmed as the durable human layer, and one framework named the shift already underway in product design.',
};

import BaseHead from '@/components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="YIL 2026-05-06 — Execution Ends, Judgment Begins | Dan Denney"
      description="Today AI tools got more room to run, information architecture was reaffirmed as the durable human layer, and one framework named the shift already underway in product design."
    />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white">
    <main class="relative z-10 bg-white shadow-xs">
      <Header />

      <!-- Hero: centered-editorial — white canvas, hairline rule beneath date, modest weight -->
      <section class="bg-white">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-24 text-center">
          <p
            class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#6a6a6a]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            2026-05-06 — Yesterday I Learned
          </p>
          <!-- Hairline rule: the single decorative element -->
          <div class="mx-auto mt-4 h-px w-16 bg-[#dddddd]"></div>
          <h1
            class="mt-8 text-[#222222]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1;"
          >
            Execution Ends, Judgment Begins
          </h1>
          <p
            class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#3f3f3f]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            Today AI tools got more room to run, information architecture was reaffirmed as the
            durable human layer, and one framework named the shift already underway in product
            design.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Capacity: cards layout, gray-100, accent-1 (Rausch #ff385c) -->
      <section class="bg-gray-100">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
          <!-- pill-h2-bar -->
          <div
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-[#ff385c]/20 bg-[#ff385c]/10 px-3 py-1"
          >
            <span
              class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#ff385c]"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >Capacity</span
            >
          </div>
          <h2
            class="mt-3 text-[#222222]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1;"
          >
            The Grid Just Got Bigger
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 h-0.5 w-12 bg-[#ff385c]"></div>

          <!-- Two equal-width cards, Airbnb shadow tier on hover -->
          <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <!-- Card 1: Claude Code -->
            <div
              class="rounded-lg border border-[#ff385c]/20 bg-white p-6 transition-shadow hover:shadow-lg"
              style="box-shadow: rgba(0,0,0,0.02) 0 0 0 1px, rgba(0,0,0,0.04) 0 2px 6px, rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 4px 8px;"
            >
              <p
                class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#ff385c]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >
                Claude Code
              </p>
              <h3
                class="mt-2 text-lg text-[#222222]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2;"
              >
                Stop Rationing, Start Moving
              </h3>
              <p
                class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[#3f3f3f]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
              >
                Effective today, Claude doubled Claude Code's 5-hour rate limits for Pro, Max, and
                Team plans, removed the peak-hours limit reduction for Pro and Max, and
                substantially raised API rate limits for Opus models. The practical shift: fewer
                sessions paused waiting for limits to reset, more tasks moving in parallel through
                the day.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2: GPT-5.5 Instant -->
            <div
              class="rounded-lg border border-[#ff385c]/20 bg-white p-6 transition-shadow hover:shadow-lg"
              style="box-shadow: rgba(0,0,0,0.02) 0 0 0 1px, rgba(0,0,0,0.04) 0 2px 6px, rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 4px 8px;"
            >
              <p
                class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#ff385c]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >
                OpenAI
              </p>
              <h3
                class="mt-2 text-lg text-[#222222]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2;"
              >
                Signal Over Noise
              </h3>
              <p
                class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[#3f3f3f]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
              >
                OpenAI is replacing the default ChatGPT model with GPT-5.5 Instant — an
                incremental upgrade aimed at reducing hallucinations in high-stakes domains like
                healthcare, law, and finance. The quieter improvement: less verbose responses.
                Ambient AI should surface what matters, not produce more text.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Quote: standalone-dark-band — near-black #222222 -->
      <section style="background: #222222;">
        <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-5xl overflow-hidden px-6 py-20">
          <div
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="pointer-events-none absolute -left-4 -top-10 select-none text-[16rem] leading-none text-white/5"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 700;"
          >
            "
          </div>
          <blockquote class="relative max-w-3xl">
            <p
              class="text-2xl text-white sm:text-3xl"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.4;"
            >
              Execution UI helps humans perform deterministic work. Judgment UI helps humans
              evaluate, guide, and correct work done by machines.
            </p>
            <footer class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="h-px w-8 bg-[#92174d]/60"></div>
              <cite
                class="not-italic text-sm text-[#6a6a6a]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
              >
                <a
                  href="https://substack.com/home/post/p-193949917"
                  class="transition-colors hover:text-white"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">Substack — Shifting Experiences</a
                >
              </cite>
            </footer>
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Foundation: prose layout, white, accent-2 (Luxe Purple #460479) -->
      <section class="bg-white">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
          <!-- pill-h2-bar -->
          <div
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-[#460479]/20 bg-[#460479]/10 px-3 py-1"
          >
            <span
              class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#460479]"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >Foundation</span
            >
          </div>
          <h2
            class="mt-3 text-[#222222]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1;"
          >
            IA Still Holds the Shape
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 h-0.5 w-12 bg-[#460479]"></div>

          <div class="mt-10 space-y-8">
            <p
              class="max-w-2xl text-base text-[#222222]"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
            >
              The Information Age's core challenges haven't changed as tools have evolved at pace:
              finding information, understanding it, using it, and trusting it. A piece from
              saturdave.com made the case that information architecture still matters precisely
              because it brings holistic, human-centric thinking to information and its use — a
              framing that accelerating AI capacity only strengthens, not erases.
            </p>

            <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
              <div class="border-t-2 border-[#460479] pt-4">
                <h3
                  class="text-sm text-[#222222]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 700;"
                >
                  Human Centricity
                </h3>
                <p
                  class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6a6a6a]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
                >
                  IA keeps the human at the center of information use — prioritizing how people
                  find, understand, and trust information over how systems prefer to organize it.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t-2 border-[#460479] pt-4">
                <h3
                  class="text-sm text-[#222222]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 700;"
                >
                  Organizational Alignment
                </h3>
                <p
                  class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6a6a6a]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
                >
                  Shared structure helps teams share meaning consistently — naming, categorizing,
                  and linking information so multiple people can navigate it the same way.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t-2 border-[#460479] pt-4">
                <h3
                  class="text-sm text-[#222222]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 700;"
                >
                  Clarity for AI
                </h3>
                <p
                  class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#6a6a6a]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
                >
                  The better the underlying information architecture, the more useful it becomes
                  for machines operating on top of it — good structure benefits both audiences.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p
              class="max-w-2xl text-base text-[#222222]"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
            >
              The throughline: IA is not a discipline threatened by AI. It is the durable human
              infrastructure layer that determines how well AI can serve.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Interface: split layout, gray-100, accent-3 (Plus Magenta #92174d) -->
      <section class="bg-gray-100">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
          <!-- pill-h2-bar -->
          <div
            class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-[#92174d]/20 bg-[#92174d]/10 px-3 py-1"
          >
            <span
              class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#92174d]"
              style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >Interface</span
            >
          </div>
          <h2
            class="mt-3 text-[#222222]"
            style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1;"
          >
            Invest in Judgment, Simplify Execution
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 h-0.5 w-12 bg-[#92174d]"></div>

          <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <!-- Left: prose + comparison table -->
            <div class="space-y-5">
              <p
                class="text-base text-[#222222]"
                style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
              >
                A Substack post on companies shifting their software experiences named a useful
                heuristic for deciding which screens to invest in, simplify, or retire.
              </p>

              <!-- Comparison table -->
              <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-[#92174d]/20">
                <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
                  <thead>
                    <tr class="bg-[#92174d]/10">
                      <th
                        scope="col"
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-[#92174d]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >UI Type</th
                      >
                      <th
                        scope="col"
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-[#92174d]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >What it does</th
                      >
                      <th
                        scope="col"
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-[#92174d]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >Trend</th
                      >
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="bg-white">
                    <tr class="border-t border-[#92174d]/10">
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-[#222222]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >Execution UI</td
                      >
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-[#3f3f3f]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
                        >Helps humans perform deterministic, repetitive work</td
                      >
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-[#6a6a6a]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
                        >Shrinking</td
                      >
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-t border-[#92174d]/10">
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-[#222222]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >Judgment UI</td
                      >
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 text-[#3f3f3f]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
                        >Helps humans evaluate, guide, and correct machine work</td
                      >
                      <td
                        class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-[#92174d]"
                        style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                        >Growing</td
                      >
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>

              <p
                class="text-base text-[#222222]"
                style="font-family: Inter, -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
              >
                The practical prompt: for each experience I create, which screens are Execution UI
                and which are Judgment UI? Where could an AI-assisted flow remove deterministic
                steps while adding better review, verification, reasoning, and correction surfaces?
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Right: HubSpot callout card -->
            <div
              class="rounded-lg border border-[#92174d]/20 bg-white p-6"
              style="box-shadow: rgba(0,0,0,0.02) 0 0 0 1px, rgba(0,0,0,0.04) 0 2px 6px, rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0 4px 8px;"
            >
              <p
                class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[#92174d]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
              >
                Case in point
              </p>
              <h3
                class="mt-2 text-base text-[#222222]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.3;"
              >
                The Seven-Screen Sales Quote
              </h3>
              <p
                class="mt-3 text-sm text-[#3f3f3f]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
              >
                Creating a single sales quote in HubSpot requires navigating seven sequential
                screens. Each screen asks a human to enter data, configure a rule, or follow a
                process step. No judgment required — the human is executing. This is an Execution
                UI fossil: built for a world before AI could handle the deterministic steps, now
                ripe for collapse into a single review surface where the human confirms rather than
                constructs.
              </p>
              <div class="mt-5 border-t border-[#92174d]/10 pt-5">
                <p
                  class="text-sm italic text-[#6a6a6a]"
                  style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;"
                >
                  "Think more about the experiences I create. How can I shift toward judgment UI?"
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- References: white -->
      <section class="bg-white">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
          <p
            class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[#6a6a6a]"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            References
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span
                class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-[#460479]/20 bg-[#460479]/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[#460479]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                >foundation</span
              >
              <a
                href="https://saturdave.com/information-architecture-still-matters/?ref=sidebar"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-sm text-[#222222] underline decoration-[#dddddd] transition-colors hover:decoration-[#460479]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
                >Information Architecture Still Matters</a
              >
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span
                class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-[#92174d]/20 bg-[#92174d]/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[#92174d]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
                >interface</span
              >
              <a
                href="https://substack.com/home/post/p-193949917"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-sm text-[#222222] underline decoration-[#dddddd] transition-colors hover:decoration-[#92174d]"
                style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
                >Shifting Experiences: Execution UI vs Judgment UI</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Design Notes -->
      <section class="border-t border-gray-200 bg-gray-100">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-12">
          <p
            class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[#6a6a6a]"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            Design Notes
          </p>
          <p
            class="mt-2 text-sm text-[#3f3f3f]"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 600;"
          >
            YIL 2026-05-06 — Execution Ends, Judgment Begins
          </p>
          <p
            class="mt-1 text-sm text-[#6a6a6a]"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            A day when AI capacity expanded, IA principles were reaffirmed as the durable human
            layer, and a sharp framework named the coming shift in interface design from execution
            to judgment.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full" style="background: #ff385c"></span>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] text-[#6a6a6a]"
                style="font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;"
                >accent-1 / text-[#ff385c] — Rausch / capacity</span
              >
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full" style="background: #460479"></span>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] text-[#6a6a6a]"
                style="font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;"
                >accent-2 / text-[#460479] — Luxe Purple / foundation</span
              >
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full" style="background: #92174d"></span>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] text-[#6a6a6a]"
                style="font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;"
                >accent-3 / text-[#92174d] — Plus Magenta / interface</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
          <p
            class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-[#6a6a6a]"
            style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;"
          >
            This design ports Airbnb's visual language — pure white canvas (#ffffff), near-black
            ink (#222222), and restrained single-accent discipline — to a day centered on
            conceptual frameworks about information and interface design. The reference's
            single-accent principle (Rausch #ff385c for primary everything) is adapted into three
            accent hues that each track one of the day's distinct themes: Rausch for the
            capacity/energy news, Luxe Purple for IA's intellectual depth, and Plus Magenta for
            the Execution→Judgment shift. What makes this day distinct from a generic blog post is
            the structural tension — the AI infrastructure news is context, while the IA and
            Judgment UI sections are the real payload — and the design makes that hierarchy
            legible through surface rhythm (news on surface, ideas on white) without spelling it
            out. Airbnb's typographic restraint (modest 500–700 weights, no display heroics) fits
            a day where the ideas carry the weight, not the layout.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
